      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "Seconding this issue for 23.0. Running bitcoind -testnet  causes Bitcoin core to crash shortly after, with no error message (updates to seemingly random tip before emptying its first cache and then KILL) This is on a generic VPS instance so I highly doubt it's a hardware issue.\r\n`2022-08-01T20:00:23Z UpdateTip: new best=00000000033238273918d98a63adcd159edcac05f3d18852d4c51da002e53b40 height=319 version=0x00000001 log2_work=40.321950 tx=320 date='2011-02-03T08:39:32Z' progress=0.000005 cache=0.1MiB(319txo)\r\n2022-08-01T20:00:23Z UpdateTip: new best=000000009db9e943c4a49e24c6034c65915d84c4bc468b9e63d847b048319b91 height=320 version=0x00000001 log2_work=40.326452 tx=321 date='2011-02-03T08:40:18Z' progress=0.000005 cache=0.1MiB(320txo)\r\nKilled`\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen I try to sync mainnet (just plain bitcoind) it crashes at roughly ~440MB cache\r\n`2022-08-01T19:50:40Z UpdateTip: new best=00000000000000507f1334c795a60d5b999526dc7cd9e76a2db15c9c9221886a height=209220 version=0x00000001 log2_work=69.065180 tx=9182639 date='2012-11-23T15:38:04Z' progress=0.012202 cache=449.0MiB(3273093txo)\r\n2022-08-01T19:50:41Z UpdateTip: new best=000000000000029ea75c5957d2716712ed475ef96ffbdf3e7e54f6de0faecd1e height=209221 version=0x00000002 log2_work=69.065213 tx=9182740 date='2012-11-23T15:42:07Z' progress=0.012202 cache=449.0MiB(3273189txo)\r\n2022-08-01T19:50:42Z UpdateTip: new best=00000000000002ea56969be76af5f5b401fdf20f81a65807e59245bbdd902145 height=209222 version=0x00000001 log2_work=69.065247 tx=9182935 date='2012-11-23T15:52:00Z' progress=0.012202 cache=449.0MiB(3273151txo)\r\n`\r\nand then it just stops, nothing in debug.log\r\n\r\nPretty sure it has to do with not being able to write? Not sure but when I lower the dbcache it crashes faster (presumably because it tries to write earlier?)",
